1.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
1.plot: Jack and Milton get an urgent message from Funderburk requesting their help one more time, so they return to the spy headquarters in Washington.

2.title: Gold Diggers
2.plot: Rudy has inherited a worthless piece of land, but Jack and Milton urge him to check it out before he sells it to a neighboring rancher.

3.title: From Zereos to Hereos
3.plot: Milton, Jerry and Joan decide to make a martial arts video as a new MA performance group called the "Tiger Trio."

4.title: The Stang
4.plot: To impress his ex-girlfriend Julie, Milton "borrows" his Dad's classic Mustang.

5.title: Nerd with a Cape
5.plot: Milton dresses up as an original superhero for a convention but is forced into action when a crisis arises and forced to ditch class. Meanwhile, Jack and Taylor fight over the smoothie table which causes Taylor to quit.

6.title: RV There Yet?
6.plot: With Jack and Milton fighting all the time, Rudy decides to take them on a camping trip in his old RV. Meanwhile, Jerry and Joan bid on a storage locker unit and find something valuable.

7.title: Invasion of the Ghost Pirates
7.plot: With an impending lunar eclipse, an old Seaford legend surfaces about a ghost pirate returning to seek his revenge on the wharf after a lunar eclipse 300 years ago led to his ship crashing into the shore. Jack makes it clear he doesn't believe in ghosts, but his skepticism is put to the test.

8.title: The Amazing Krupnick
8.plot: Jack and Jerry learn that Milton is a talented magician.

9.title: The Battle of Seaford Hill
9.plot: Jerry sets out to prove his great, great grandfather was a true war hero.

10.title: Fight at the Museum
10.plot: Milton and Jerry volunteer at the Seaford History Museum in an attempt to win over the same girl but when they discover the museum is being robbed and the girl of their dreams is in danger, they have to work to save her and the museum.

11.title: Tightroping the Shark
11.plot: Jack and Milton recruit legendary daredevil Spanky Danger to raise money for the troubled Seaford Aquarium.

12.title: Full Metal Jack
12.plot: Jack, Jerry, and Milton form a team to compete in a Commando Paintball Challenge.

13.title: Martinez & Malone: Mall Cops!
13.plot: Jerry quits his job at the bowling alley and joins Joan as a mall cop.

14.title: Seaford Hustle
14.plot: Milton meets Tom, the President of a powerful brotherhood. Kim visits Seaford and Jack envisions himself saving her from the forces taking her away.

15.title: Kickin It in the Office
15.plot: A documentary film crew from the Karate Channel comes to film a typical day in the dojo. Meanwhile, Milton finally takes a stand against Jerry's recurring pranks by executing the ultimate prank.

16.title: Bringing Down the House
16.plot: The gang decide to buy themselves a boat but they run out of money and come up with an alternate plan.

17.title: You Don't Know Jack
17.plot: When Jerry disrespects Jack's authority as a sensei and throws an unauthorized party at the dojo, Jack suspends him from taking his black belt test.

18.title: The Grandmaster
18.plot: Kim returns from Japan with her sensei, Tomo, who's interested in hiring Rudy.

1.title: Wasabi Warriors
1.plot: The gang meets a skater with martial arts skills.

2.title: Fat Chance
2.plot: Milton's life is saved by the school's janitor, who turns out to be a former sumo champion. Rudy and Lonnie fight over a storage space in the basement.

3.title: Dummy Dancing
3.plot: Eddie is blackmailed by Turner to play pranks.

5.title: Swords and Magic
5.plot: Milton's nerd friends abandon him before a big role-play battle. The gang eventually decide to come to his aid.

6.title: Road to Wasabi
6.plot: Rudy throws himself a surprise birthday party.

7.title: All the Wrong Moves
7.plot: Jerry signs the gang up for a dance competition, except they can't dance. When his new dance troupe betray him, he must quickly teach the group to dance. Rudy and Marge make a product called the pocket ninja.

8.title: Ricky Weaver
8.plot: Pop sensation Ricky Weaver comes to the school for a concert after Kim won a contest, but when Jack warns Kim about Ricky's plans she doesn't believe him. Rudy, Milton, Jerry and Eddie form a boyband called "Black Belt Boyz".

9.title: Wax on Wax off
9.plot: Bobby Wasabi sends over a special gift - a life-sized statue of himself!

10.title: The Commercial
10.plot: After taking an improv acting class, Rudy auditions for a role in a commercial. However, Jack unintentionally sabotages the audition, landing the role for himself. Kim and Eddie help Milton bake a cake after he fails the class.

11.title: Kung Fu Cop
11.plot: When Jack falls asleep watching a movie, he imagines him and the gang are in the 70's cop film.

12.title: Boo Gi Nights
12.plot: The gang host a Halloween party at the mall, but when the black dragons find out Jack's one fear, they ruin the party. Rudy meets a mysterious woman.

13.title: Clash of the Titans
13.plot: Milton falls for a girl named Julie, who's uncle happens to be Ty, the sensei of the black dragon dojo! Jack and Kim try to resolve the feud between Rudy and Ty. Jerry and Eddie compete in a rap battle.

14.title: Badge of Honor
14.plot: After Milton accidentally stops a robbery at the mall, he becomes an honorary mall cop, but this causes trouble when he starts to betray his friends. Jack and Kim try to teach Rudy how to skateboard.

15.title: The Great Escape
15.plot: Milton pulls a prank at school, but Jerry takes the blaim, landing him in high security detention. The gang must find a way to break him out, so he can compete in a karate tournament that his family have come to see.

16.title: Dude Where's My Sword
16.plot: When Rudy goes on a bike trip with Bobby and Phil, the gang throw a party at the dojo. All is well until they notice Rudy's prized katana sword is missing. Jack, Kim and Milton try to find a new one, while Jerry and Eddie clean up.

17.title: Breaking Board
17.plot: Jack accidently kicks Jerry in the ribs and insists he go to the hospital.

18.title: Reality Fights
18.plot: The gang participate in Bobby's new game show, but it tears them apart and tests their loyalty to each other.

19.title: Kickin' It in China
19.plot: Jack is invited to the junior martial arts championships in China, but while there runs into his enemy. Jerry, Milton and Eddie go on an adventure to find out the ending of a fortune.

20.title: The Wrath of Swan
20.plot: Jack declines Kim's invite to a dance, so she takes a new boy at school, who turns out to be a black dragon. Milton and Jerry discover they have hot dates. Rudy and Eddie make cars for a scout competition.

21.title: Rowdy Rudy
21.plot: Rudy flips a pro wrestler and goes viral, which makes Jack think it's acceptable to fight people at school, which lands him in detention. Milton worries when he thinks his girlfriend wants to kiss him.

1.title: Rock'em Sock'em Rudy
1.plot: Bobby unveils a new robot sensei, which greatly improves the gang's performances. Rudy is fired, but when the robot starts pushing them too hard, they try to get Rudy back. Milton and Eddie create their own robot.

2.title: My Left Foot
2.plot: Milton kicks a football sky-high, making him the new star of the team.

3.title: We Are Family
3.plot: Jerry gets a job at the Meatball King to help the gang buy a go-cart.

4.title: Eddie Cries Uncle
4.plot: Eddie lies about having a famous uncle.

5.title: Skate Rat
5.plot: The gang convinces Jack's hero, Luke Sampson, to build them a skate park.

7.title: It Takes Two to Tangle
7.plot: Rudy and Jack attend a student/sensei tournament.

8.title: Buddyguards
8.plot: Jack and Jerry are bummed when they can't get tickets to see Izzy Gunnar.

9.title: Dojo Daycare
9.plot: The gang decides to turn the dojo into a daycare center.

10.title: Indiana Eddie
10.plot: Eddie is the only one to take his career assessment seriously.

11.title: Kim of Kong
11.plot: Jack lies to get out of working on a project so he can play a game.

12.title: Kickin It Old School
12.plot: Rudy needs to earn his diploma!

13.title: The Chosen One
13.plot: The gang gets the opportunity of a lifetime.

14.title: Hit the Road Jack
14.plot: Jack is offered a scholarship to a prestigious facility.

15.title: A Slip Down Memory Lane
15.plot: Jack slips on a stack of bo staffs and loses all memory of his friends.

16.title: Wedding Crashers
16.plot: Bobby Wasabi is lonely while his ninjas are away.

17.title: Wazombie Warriors
17.plot: Kim goes to a zombie movie and falls asleep, and has a scary dream.

18.title: Sole-Brothers
18.plot: Jack helps Jerry get a job at the mall.

20.title: New Jack City
20.plot: Carson, an old friend of the gang and Rudy's former star student, returns to Seaford. His own martial arts moves prompt Rudy to replace Jack with Carson in the upcoming tournament, annoying Jack.

21.title: Karate Games
21.plot: A Hollywood director casts Jack and Kim as the stars of his next movie.

22.title: Kickin' It On Our Own
22.plot: Rudy makes the hardest decision of his life.

23.title: Oh, Christmas Nuts!
23.plot: The gang volunteers at the Santa attraction in the mall.

1.title: Spyfall
1.plot: Phil is mistaken for a hitman. Jack goes under cover as a special agent to try to stop the real hitman. Meanwhile Jerry is trying to help Joan get her job back as the mall security guard.

2.title: Dueling Dojos
2.plot: Rudy is asked to babysit Grandmaster Po's nephew.

3.title: Glove Hurts
3.plot: Milton's project takes first place at the school invention fair.

4.title: The Sub Sinker
4.plot: Jerry "the Sub Sinker" Martinez drives away yet another substitute teacher.

5.title: Meet the McKrupnicks
5.plot: When the gang goes with Milton to a family reunion they awaken an old feud.

6.title: Witless Protection
6.plot: The gang testifies against a notorious criminal.

7.title: Jack Stands Alone
7.plot: Kim tries to get Frank expelled after he kidnaps the school turtle.

8.title: Two Dates and a Funeral
8.plot: Jack and Kim admit that they have feelings for each other.

9.title: Win, Lose or Ty
9.plot: Everyone is forced to live under one roof.

10.title: Sensei and Sensibility
10.plot: The owner of Super Kicks offers Jack an opportunity to be a sensei.

11.title: Gabby's Gold
11.plot: When Kim's gymnastics coach quits, Gabby Douglas steps in.

12.title: The New Girl
12.plot: Jack and Kim help Rudy recruit a prized female student to join the dojo.

13.title: Fawlty Temple
13.plot: Rudy, Jerry and Milton transform the Shaolin Temple into a resort hotel.

14.title: Seaford, We Have a Problem
14.plot: Milton is offered a trip to space by SASA when Jerry accidentally goes instead, while the others attempt to find a scam in bingo.

15.title: Temple of Doom
15.plot: Milton agrees to watch the temple while the monks are out.

16.title: Mama Mima
16.plot: When the gang learns that Phil hasn't seen his mother in years, they invite her to Seaford.

17.title: Home Alone at School
17.plot: After Jerry's latest prank lands Kim and Jack in detention, he must work to regain their trust.

18.title: School of Jack
18.plot: Jack recruits the kids from Milton's "Classical Music Club" to form a rock band.

19.title: Queen of Karts
19.plot: When Kim shatters the record at the go-kart track, she decides to compete in the Seaford 500.

20.title: How Bobby Got His Groove Back
20.plot: The gang's life at the dojo gets turned upside down when Bobby Wasabi moves in after his self-financed action film bombs and he loses everything.

21.title: Return of Spyfall
21.plot: Jack and Milton learn that Principal Funderburk is actually a secret agent tasked with putting together an "A-team" of talented teens.

22.title: Wasabi Forever
22.plot: Rudy reminds the gang that, while they can move on from the dojo itself, they will always be bound by the Wasabi Code.

imdb.plot outline: Set at the Bobby Wasabi Martial Arts Academy, a strip mall martial arts studio and worst dojo in the under-performing nationwide Bobby Wasabi chain. Revolves around a ragtag crew of lovable misfits who welcome a hotshot skateboarder named Jack who will teach them about life, karate, and how to just plain kick it.

plot: A once-in-a-generation young karate fighter named Jack joins the Wasabi warriors.

Rudy is a down-on-his-luck martial arts teacher who is only in teaching of his students, Milton, Jerry, and Eddie. Things begin to turn around for him when he meets Jack, a young, but very good martial artist, who has a connection with famous martial arts movie star, Bobby Wasabi. Jack agrees to help win back the dojo in a tournament against a rival dojo, the Black Dragons. While on many crazy adventures, Jack and the gang stick together with the Bobby Wasabi code, while working with former Black Dragon trainee, Kim
synopsis: Run by Sensei Rudy, the Bobby Wasabi Martial Arts Academy is the worst dojo in the nationwide Bobby Wasabi chain and is in danger of closing. But things change when Jack reluctantly joins the dojo and meets his new crew, including tough guy slacker Jerry and confident martial arts expert Kim. The crew teaches a group of neighborhood goofballs about life, karate and how to "kick it." Jack and the gang quickly realize their newfound friendship will take them places they've never imagined and, united, they can become unstoppable.
